#Description of the input datasets
##Crop Types (data/crops/merged_*.csv)
###‘crops’ - Annual weighted mean Crop Yield and Area

Description: Germany-wide, annual crop dataset (1979–2021) with 11 crop types: spring barley, winter barley, grain maize, silage maize, oats, potatoes, winter rapeseed, rye, sugar beet, triticale, winter wheat.
Columns: of ‘Final_data.csv’, used for the preprocessing: Year, Crop, Area [ha], Yield [t/ha]
Spatial resolution: NUTS-3 districts (~900 km² on average)
Preprocessing:
Mapped each exploratory to corresponding NUTS-3 regions
Computed weighted crop area and yield per region using CORINE-derived weights
Pivoted data so that Area and Yield are separate columns
Filled missing years to create continuous time series using CORINE base years (2006, 2012, 2018)
Overview and explanations of the column names of the files merged_*.csv:
Column Name	Description
year	Year of observation
var	Crop type or category (e.g., wheat, barley, district)
measure	Type of measurement: ‘yield’ [t/ha] or ‘area’ [ha]
weighted_value_sum	Weighted value of the measurement per region/crop
###Insects
Preprocessing:
Dataset with ID 21969 (Grasslands) was filtered with corresponding dataset ds26008, as recommended by the responsibles of Biodiversity Exploratories.
Dataset with ID 22007 (Forests) without further preprocessing
Overview and explanations of the column names of ds21969_filtered.csv (according to Weisser et. al ((2025)):
Column Name	Description	DataType
TrapID	ID including Plot, Trap type, Month and Year	string
Exploratory	Exploratory	string
PlotID	ID of experimental plot (HEG, SEG, AEG, 1–50 each)	string
Traptype	Trap specification (KEF = Sweep net, 60 double-sweeps/plot)	string
CollectionMonth	Sampling month	string
CollectionYear	Sampling year	date-yyyy
VIP_EP	VIP or Ep	string
Order	Taxonomic order of each species	string
Suborder	Taxonomic suborder of each species	string
Family	Taxonomic family of each species	string
Species	Species name according to Fauna Europaea	string
NumberAdults	Number of adult individuals per species (NA = missing data)	integer
Overview and explanations of the column names of ds22007.csv:
VariableName	Description	DataType
TrapID_run	ID including Plot, Subplot, Trap type, CollectionRun and Year	string
Exploratory	Exploratory (ALB, HAI, SCH)	string
PlotID	ID of experimental plot (HEW, SEW, AEW, 1–50 each)	string
Traptype	Trap specification (FFB = cross-window trap, 60×40 cm, top and bottom jar, 150 cm height)	string
CollectionRun	One of six sampling events (A–F) between April and October	string
CollectionYear	Sampling year	date-yyyy
VIP_EP	VIP indicator	string
Priority	Indicator of analysed trap per plot and month (randomly selected traps)	double
Order	Taxonomic order of each species	string
Suborder	Taxonomic suborder of each species	string
Family	Taxonomic family of each species	string
Species	Species name according to Fauna Europaea	string
NumberAdults	Number of adult individuals per species (NA = missing data)	integer
###Vegetation-based Remote Sensing Indices (data/NDVI/, data/NDMI/, data/NIRv/)
Remote sensing indices were calculated from Landsat 7 Level 2 (Collection 2, Tier 1) imagery (2008–2019) using the Google Earth Engine (GEE) JavaScript API.

Spatial resolution: 30 m
Temporal resolution: 16 days
Processing steps:
Uploaded BE borders as feature collections
Cloud masking using the QA_PIXEL band
Vegetation mask applied (NDVI ≥ 0.2)
Monthly mean index values calculated per region
Only valid pixels included in the mean
If no valid pixels: value set to -9999
NIRv scaled by 1/10,000
Overview and explanations of the column names of ‘Landsat7_Monthly_NDMI_ALB_merged.csv’:
(NDMI, NDVI, NIRv have an analogous structure)

Column Name	Description	Data Type
system:index	Internal index generated by Google Earth Engine	integer
mean_NDMI	Monthly mean NDMI value per region (valid pixels only)	float
month	Month of observation (1–12)	integer
region	Exploratory region (ALB, HAI, SCH)	string
year	Year of observation	integer
.geo	Geometry metadata from GEE export (not used in analysis)	string
Crop Types (data/smi/smi_means_*.csv)
Source: UFZ Drought Monitor Germany (1951–present)
Based on a meso-scale hydrological model mHM
Provides monthly total soil (0–180 cm) and topsoil (0–25 cm) SMI values
Values range from 0 to 1, representing percentile-based soil moisture relative to historical distribution
Preprocessing Steps:
Converted netCDF to data frame using R (terra package)
Clipped dataset to BE extent using Python (rioxarray)
Extracted coordinates and time information
Aggregated monthly values per region (ALB, HAI, SCH) for analysis
Overview and explanations of Soil Moisture Index (SMI) Dataset (data/smi/merged_*.csv):
Column Name	Description	Data Type
time	Date of observation (format: YYYY-MM-DD)	date
ALB	SMI value for ALB region	float
HAI	SMI value for HAI region	float
SCH	SMI value for SCH region	float
###Weather
This dataset contains monthly weather and soil measurements per plot and region.

Overview and explanations of the column names of ‘bexis_weather_plots.csv’ (according to Wöllauer et al. (2021)):
Column Name	Description	Data Type
plotID	Experimental plot identifier (e.g., AEG03)	string
datetime	Date of measurement (YYYY-MM-DD)	date
precipitation_radolan	Total monthly precipitation (mm)	float
precipitation_radolan_rain_days	Number of days with rainfall	integer
rH_200	Relative humidity at 200 cm	float
rH_200_max	Maximum relative humidity at 200 cm	float
rH_200_min	Minimum relative humidity at 200 cm	float
SM_10	Soil moisture at 10 cm depth	float
SM_20	Soil moisture at 20 cm depth	float
Ta_10	Air temperature at 10 cm depth	float
Ta_10_max	Maximum air temperature at 10 cm	float
Ta_10_min	Minimum air temperature at 10 cm	float
Ta_200	Air temperature at 200 cm	float
Ta_200_max	Maximum air temperature at 200 cm	float
Ta_200_min	Minimum air temperature at 200 cm	float
Ts_05	Soil temperature at 5 cm depth	float
Ts_05_max	Maximum soil temperature at 5 cm	float
Ts_05_min	Minimum soil temperature at 5 cm	float
Ts_10	Soil temperature at 10 cm depth	float
Ts_10_max	Maximum soil temperature at 10 cm	float
Ts_10_min	Minimum soil temperature at 10 cm	float
Ts_20	Soil temperature at 20 cm depth	float
Ts_20_max	Maximum soil temperature at 20 cm	float
Ts_20_min	Minimum soil temperature at 20 cm	float
Ts_50	Soil temperature at 50 cm depth	float
Ts_50_max	Maximum soil temperature at 50 cm	float
Ts_50_min	Minimum soil temperature at 50 cm	float
year	Year of observation	integer
month	Month of observation	integer
region	Exploratory region (ALB, HAI, SCH)	string
Notes:
- Missing values are marked as NA.
- Measurements cover air and soil temperature, relative humidity, soil moisture, and precipitation.
- Used as environmental predictors in Granger causality analyses.

###Fertilization (fertilizer_cropland_means.csv)
This dataset contains annual fertilizer application rates [kg/ha] for main crop types and nutrients in the study regions.

Preprocessing Steps:
1. Cropping: Raster files cropped to the extent of each exploratory shapefile.
2. Aggregation: Mean raster value calculated per year, crop type, fertilizer, and region.

Overview and explanations of the column names of ‘fertilizer_cropland_means.csv’:
Column Name	Description	Data Type
Year	Year of observation	integer
Croptype	Crop type (e.g., Fiber crops, Maize, Wheat, etc.)	string
Fertilizer	Nutrient type (N, K2O, P2O5)	string
ALB	Fertilizer amount in kg/ha for ALB region	float
HAI	Fertilizer amount in kg/ha for HAI region	float
SCH	Fertilizer amount in kg/ha for SCH region	float
Germany Mosaic (mosaic_zones_means.csv)
This dataset provides annual landscape metrics for each study region, derived from Germany-wide satellite data (1984–2023). Largely homogeneous image areas (“zones”) are delineated as polygons, and four structural metrics are calculated per region and year.

Preprocessing Steps:
1. Data acquisition: Germany Mosaic data cube (1984–2023) downloaded with raster and vector products from Landsat platforms 4, 5, 8, 9.
2. Clipping: Zones clipped to the extent of each exploratory 3. Area-weighted aggregation: Annual mean values per region

Overview and explanations of the column names of ‘mosaic_zones_means.csv’ according to Selsam et al. (2025):
Column Name	Description	Data Type
region	Study region (ALB, HAI, SCH)	string
year	Year of observation	integer
cellsize	Size of the zone (ha); indicates spatial extent of homogeneous areas	float
dendrites	Perimeter-to-area ratio; measure of shape complexity of a zone	float
normal	Normalized density of zone structure; indicates structural organization	float
relation	Quotient of neighbors to perimeter; measure of connectivity within a zone	float
Structure of R-script folders for Granger Causality analysis workflow:
stationarity_detrend_scripts/
├── ADF_KPSS_test.R
│ └─ Description: Performs stationarity tests on all datasets (monthly and yearly resolution), recommends transformations
│ **OUTPUT:** -> tables/stationarity_test – CSV tables with test results per dataset 
├── detrending_monthly.R
│ └─ Description: Detrending and/or differencing for monthly data, performs stationarity tests on detrended and or differenced data, recommends transformations
│ **OUTPUT:** -> tables/detrend_diff_stationarity
└── detrending_yearly.R
└─ Description: Detrending and/or differencing for yearly data, performs stationarity tests on detrended and or differenced data, recommends transformations 
  **OUTPUT:** -> tables/detrend_diff_stationarity 

granger_causality_monthly/
├── granger_causality_monthly.R
│ ├─ Description: Tests Granger causality (monthly) for all originally stationary time series, tested in 'ADF_KPSS_test'
│ ├─ **INPUT:**
│ │ - tables/stationarity_test/combined_stationarity_ds21969_ALB_HAI_monthly.csv
│ │ - tables/stationarity_test/combined_stationarity_ds21969_SCH_monthly.csv
│ │ - tables/stationarity_test/combined_stationarity_ds22007_monthly.csv
│ └─ **OUTPUT:** -> tables/granger_test/ – CSV tables with Granger causality test results for all family x environmental combinations.

├── 2nd_granger_ds21969_monthly.R
│ ├─ Description: Tests Granger causality for grassland plots (ds21969)in monthly resolution with originally stationary data + data that derived stationarity through detrending and/or differencing.
│ ├─ **INPUT:**
│ │ - tables/stationarity_test/combined_stationarity_ds21969_ALB_HAI_monthly.csv
│ │ - tables/stationarity_test/combined_stationarity_ds21969_SCH_monthly.csv
│ │ - tables/detrend_diff_stationarity/stationarity_table_ds21969_detrended_monthly.csv
│ │ - tables/detrend_diff_stationarity/stationarity_table_ds21969_diff_monthly.csv
│ │ - tables/detrend_diff_stationarity/stationarity_table_ds21969_both_monthly.csv
│ └─ **OUTPUT:** -> tables/granger_test/ – CSV results for grassland plots.

├── 2nd_granger_ds22007_monthly.R
│ ├─ Description: Tests Granger causality for forest plots (ds22007)in monthly resolution with originally stationary data + data that derived stationarity through detrending and/or differencing.
│ ├─ **INPUT:**
│ │ - tables/stationarity_test/combined_stationarity_ds22007_monthly.csv
│ │ - tables/detrend_diff_stationarity/stationarity_table_ds22007_detrended_monthly.csv
│ │ - tables/detrend_diff_stationarity/stationarity_table_ds22007_diff_monthly.csv
│ │ - tables/detrend_diff_stationarity/stationarity_table_ds22007_both_monthly.csv
│ └─ **OUTPUT:** -> tables/granger_test/ – CSV results for forest plots.

granger_causality_yearly/
├── granger_causality_yearly.R
│ ├─ Description: Tests Granger causality (yearly) for all originally stationary time series, tested in 'ADF_KPSS_test'.
│ ├─ **INPUT*:*
│ │ - tables/stationarity_test/combined_stationarity_ds21969_yearly.csv
│ │ - tables/stationarity_test/combined_stationarity_ds22007_yearly.csv
│ └─ **OUTPUT:** -> tables/granger_test/ – CSV tables with Granger causality test results for all family x environmental combinations.

├── 2nd_granger_ds21969_yearly.R
│ ├─ Description: Tests Granger causality for grassland plots (ds21969) in yearly resolution with originally stationary data + data derived through detrending and/or differencing.
│ ├─ **INPUT:**
│ │ - tables/stationarity_test/combined_stationarity_ds21969_yearly.csv
│ │ - tables/detrend_diff_stationarity/stationarity_table_ds21969_detrended_yearly.csv
│ │ - tables/detrend_diff_stationarity/stationarity_table_ds21969_diff_yearly.csv
│ │ - tables/detrend_diff_stationarity/stationarity_table_ds21969_both_yearly.csv
│ └─ **OUTPUT:** -> tables/granger_test/ – CSV results for grassland plots.

└── 2nd_granger_ds22007_yearly.R
├─ Description: Tests Granger causality for forest plots (ds22007) in yearly resolution with originally stationary data + data derived through detrending and/or differencing.
├─ **INPUT:**
│ - tables/stationarity_test/combined_stationarity_ds22007_yearly.csv
│ - tables/detrend_diff_stationarity/stationarity_table_ds22007_detrended_yearly.csv
│ - tables/detrend_diff_stationarity/stationarity_table_ds22007_diff_yearly.csv
│ - tables/detrend_diff_stationarity/stationarity_table_ds22007_both_yearly.csv
└─ **OUTPUT:** -> tables/granger_test/ – CSV results for forest plots.

plot_scripts/
├── data_description.R
│ ├─ Description: Creates species- and order-based bar plots, interactive line graphs per location and year, and generates LaTeX-compatible tables for order, family, and species.
│ └─ **OUTPUT:** -> plots/interactive_insect_plots/ – PNGs and interactive HTML plots

├── facetplots_time-series.R
│ ├─ Description: Creates faceted annual trends for insect abundance combined with all environmental variables per region (ALB, HAI, SCH). Units are harmonized across variables for comparability.
│ └─ **OUTPUT:** -> plots/facetplots/ – A4-sized PNGs

├── fertilization_linear_regression.R
│ ├─ Description: Creates log-linear regression plots for insect family abundance (grassland and forest) with at least one Granger causal result and fertilization data. Calculates annual growth rates, visualizes trends by trophic group or croptype (at least one value > 0.5 kg/ha) over 2008–2019.
│ └─ **OUTPUT:** -> plots/linear_regression/ – PNGs

├── insect_family_species_heatmap_rt.R
│ ├─ Description: Calculates intrinsic growth rate ($r_t$) of insect populations at family and species level for grasslands and forests. Builds heat maps of annual growth rates over intervals.
│ └─ **OUTPUT:** -> plots/heatmaps_rt/ – PNG files for families and species

├── plots_granger_results.R
│ ├─ Description: Prepares Granger causality test results for grassland and forest plots.Aggregates results, and creates color-coded heat maps for annual and monthly resolutions per region, chooses lag with highest F-value to be displayed in heatmap.
│ └─ **OUTPUT:** -> plots/granger_results/ – heat maps PNGs

└── sensitivity_analysis.R
├─ Description: Analyzes sensitivity of Granger causality results across lags, temporal resolutions (yearly vs. monthly), and preprocessing methods (Original, Detrended, Differenced) for two datasets and multiple regions.
└─ **OUTPUT:** -> plots/sensitivity_analysis/ – Summary plots of causal proportions
Structure of OUTPUT tables:
tables/stationarity_test/combined_stationarity_*_*.csv:
also analogous to tables in tables/detrend_diff_stationarity -
Column Name	Description
statistic_adf	Test statistic from the Augmented Dickey-Fuller (ADF) test, which checks for unit roots (non-stationarity).
p_value_adf	p-value corresponding to the ADF test statistic. Low p-values (<0.05) indicate rejection of the null hypothesis of non-stationarity.
status_adf	Interpretation of ADF result (stationary or non-stationary).
Croptype	Crop type (if applicable for crop-related datasets; NA for environmental indices like SMI).
Fertilizer	Fertilizer type (if applicable; NA for datasets not related to fertilization).
region	Geographical region of the dataset (if applicable).
var	Name of the environmental variable being tested (e.g., NDVI, NDMI, NIRv; NA if not applicable).
measure	Type of measurement for the variable (e.g., yield, area; NA if not applicable).
Exploratory	Specific exploratory site (e.g., ALB, HAI, SCH; often redundant with variable).
Family	Insect family (if applicable; NA for environmental or soil datasets).
statistic_kpss	Test statistic from the KPSS (Kwiatkowski-Phillips-Schmidt-Shin) test, which tests for trend stationarity.
p_value_kpss	p-value corresponding to the KPSS test statistic. Low p-values (<0.05) indicate rejection of the null hypothesis of stationarity.
status_kpss	Interpretation of KPSS result (stationary or non-stationary).
recommended_action	Recommended preprocessing to achieve stationarity based on the combined ADF and KPSS results. Possible categories:
• Apply differencing: ADF = stationary & KPSS = non-stationary
• Detrend: ADF = non-stationary & KPSS = stationary
• No transformation required: ADF = stationary & KPSS = stationary
• Detrend and then difference: ADF = non-stationary & KPSS = non-stationary
• Indeterminate: any other combination.
###Granger Causality Output Columns, e.g., granger_test/results_ds22007_SCH_2nd_round.csv:
Column Name	Description
Family	Insect family tested for causal relationships.
EnvDataset	Environmental dataset used as predictor (e.g., SMI_total, NDVI, NDMI, NIRv).
EnvColumn	Specific variable/column from the environmental dataset (e.g., HAI, ALB, SCH).
Croptype	Crop type if applicable (NA for datasets not related to crops).
Fertilizer	Fertilizer type if applicable (NA for datasets not related to fertilization).
Lag	Time lag tested in the Granger causality test (e.g., 1, 2, 3 months or years).
F_stat	F-statistic from the Granger causality test. NA if test could not be performed.
p_value	p-value corresponding to the F-statistic. NA if test could not be performed.
causality	Outcome of the test:
• causal – Granger causality detected (p < 0.05)
• non-causal – No Granger causality detected (p ≥ 0.05)
• no_test – Test could not be performed, e.g., due to insufficient data or missing values.
###Comments:
Note, that the scripts and the results of the 2nd of Granger Tests are complete without the ones from the 1st round of Granger Tests. The latter are rather a result of “work in progress”.

